Patch Set 3:

Hi Zhi,

I just tried downloading an independent tool for graphviz and since it was like another programming language to learn I decided to not spend much time with it.  I also went to http://www.graphviz.org/ several times to see if they had a WYSIWYG tool and it just timed out for me.

So, either I can leave the generated PNG diagram in with the visio source file or just pull it out all together. I could also look at switching to ASCII art.

Thanks,
Travis
Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

Thank Travis,

This looks great. Just what we need. 

Could you please put DocImpact flag to your commit message so that the doc team gets flagged about this change as well.
Uploaded patch set 4.

Patch Set 4:

Brian - Thanks for your previous +1

zhiyan - I know you +1 already, but I went ahead and addressed your binary file concern for the diagram source by switching the diagram to inline ASCII art.  I hope this helps.

Erno - I went ahead and added DocImpact.  Also added several Related-Bug tags that were already open against OpenStack manuals.

I hope that we can go ahead and get this doc change up so that we have the metadefs concepts live on the developer doc sites.
